        		<br/>
                <h4 style="color:grey;"><label style="display: flex; justify-content: center;color:#23bacf; font-size:25px">Entities</label><br/>
                <b>Goods and Services</b> - These entities represent all goods and services that can be sold or provided online or offline. The categories of physical items are the same as those at any eCommerce website and retail outlet selling essential, non-essential or luxury items. By services, we mean consumer services that can be sub-divided into several categories, but we focus mostly on those that require enough face-time or interaction with the clients. For instance, online consultation, coaching or counselling. <br/>
                <br/><b>Stores and Fulfilment Centers</b> - These are primary aggregators of the products and services by which they will be available to customers or clients for purchase or booking. The stores and FCs are also treated as individual objects and the important data for configuration and control of the buying or booking process, are collected during their creation. The storefront can be built using our Page Builder tool. This will have the "Add to cart" or "Buy Now" button that will be integrated with the merchant's chosen payment modes. <br/>
                <br/><b>Delivery Services</b> - Logistics is an integral part of a supply chain that controls any online or offline retail business. It is an operationally difficult problem that involves managing executives and carriers at the ground-level. We aim to provide a way for having both internal as well as third-party delivery services at hyperlocal, national and international ranges.<br/>
                <br/><b>Personnel</b> - This represents the people resources of the organization that belong to various roles at stores, FCs or IT division.<br/>
                <br/><b>Online Call/Chat & Manual Order</b> - These are created once the ordering or scheduling process is completed by providing the essential information, followed by which the product or the online/offline service is ready to get delivered. Details of the deliverable are communicated via notifications to all concerned parties. These include product or call details, important dates, and links or passcode for the online meeting or demo before purchase. <br/>
                <br/><br/>
                <label style="display: flex; justify-content: center;color:#23bacf; font-size:25px">Pricing, Promotions & Marketing</label><br/>
                <b>Pricing Rules</b> - Using a number of parameters determining consumer behaviour, a pricing rule as a criteria can be applied to any product or service to alter the price accordingly, while being sold via store(s), email campaigns, influencer endorsements or social media. <br/>
                <br/><b>Promotions</b> - To compete with other sellers and service providers, merchants use promotions to ensure customer loyalty. We have identified <b>Coupons, Vouchers and eGift Cards</b> as the primary means for providing special discounted prices and free products or services, or for attracting new customers to a store or a brand.<br/>
                <br/><b>Marketing</b> - This is an aggregation of the latest social media accounts, matching influencers and email subscribers for sending promotional content about products, services, flash sales, offers etc. to potential and existing customers.<br/>
                <br/><br/>
                <label style="display: flex; justify-content: center;color:#23bacf; font-size:25px">Operations & Infrastructure</label><br/>
                <b>File and Data Management</b> - We aim to provide an easy to use, intuitive, BUI for accessing MySQL, Postgres, Cassandra, Redis or MongoDB. As of now, only MySQL is being handled.<br/>The same interface should allow storing and modifying text and multimedia files - <b>CSV/MS Excel, PDFs, Images, Videos or 3D files</b> storing data or representing an entity - product models, services, stores, contracts, reports, plans & layouts, architecture, etc.</b><br/>
                <br/><b>Product and Service Import</b> - This is a tool to generate an HTML of a product or a service that is published at a popular eCommerce website or a service listing portal. Importing is an integral part of dropshipping and affiliate marketing. Our tool will give the flexibility to add or edit the the product or service details like prices & charges, description and multmedia before adding to the internal catalogue, so it can be listed as a regular inventory product, apart from providing an embeddable HTML.<br/>
                <br/><b>Builder (Microsites)</b> - This is an independent Javascript project for creating nested forms, tables for a MySQL database, apart from simple or advanced reports and pages. These can be embeded into other HTML pages or email body for sharing or collecting data via marketing campaigns.<br/>
                <br/><b>Inventory & Logistics Management</b> - We are providing an interface to edit inventory of products, place Purchase or Transfer orders for moving inventory in between entities viz. stores & FCs or Warehouses. Also a way to track their movement while delivering orders to customers or in between suppliers & merchant owned facilities.<br/>
                <br/><b>Payments</b> - This is an aggregation of the latest and best payment methods for hyperlocal, national and international orders in the traditional offline retail, eCommerce, or dropshipping websites.<br/>
                <br/><b>Notifications Management</b> - This is a core functionality that will help in notifying about an event or a request that updates or adds some data to the database tables. Otherwise, it will alert customers, partners, personnel or the merchant about statuses or any urgent situation that requires action. For instance, during order processing, logistics or inventory updates.
