<div class="row" style="display: flex; justify-content: center;margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px;">
<div class="col-lg-12 bg-default bg-white py-0" style="margin-bottom:10px;margin-top:10px;;">
<h4 style="color:grey;"> The data is going to be accessible in a controlled manner via UI and API of the application. But some of the data will not be accessible for updation or deletion. 
This is going to belong to those operations that trigger an event like an order that is placed by a customer or a merchant. 
Any modifications required will have to follow a standard procedure or policy that is decided and configured by the merchant.<br/><br/>
The entire application will follow a topology where the company will function as the root of the organizational tree, followed by one or more stores to which other entities will be assigned.<br/><br/>
Data in the form of CSV or an MS Excel sheet should readily be consumed for feeding data into any of the database tables that allow access via UI or API, after creation of the associated entities.
<br/><br/>Database maintenance functions can also be eased if we do not require the user to install any other 3rd party application, other than the browser that is available in any device.
</h4>

</div>
