<div class="col-lg-12 bg-default bg-white py-0" style="margin-bottom:10px;margin-top:10px;;">
<h4 style="color:grey;">Following the topology of the application, the centralized and distributed data management is meant to handle concurrent database access, serverless microservices architecture, and an event-based model in the best possible way.
<br/> We wish to save the store and FC properties in a distributed fashion while handling events centrally so that all functions and entities can take actions according to their individual logic in response to another event triggered by an entity viz. product, store, customer or the organization(hub).

</h4>

