<div class="container" id="devtools">
<p style="display: flex; justify-content: left;font-weight:bold;"> <font size="5px" color="#23bacf"><u>Tech Stack & Dev Tools</u></font></p>

<div class="row" style="display: flex; justify-content: center;margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px;">
<div class="col-lg-12 bg-default bg-white py-0" style="margin-bottom:10px;margin-top:10px;;">
<h4 style="color:grey;">The tech stack is mostly Javascript, Python & Core Java related, with databases, standard frameworks and libraries. 
We will continue using several free and open-source code projects to develop the pieces fast till we finalize on each feature, which will be decided as we get our users' feedback. 
We are not in favor of using cloud hosted services like in Computer Vision or Image recognition provided by the best in industry. Instead we consider using open-source projects that give fairly good results.<br/>
We want even those users handling sensitive data and executing all their services only on-premise, to try our application and customize it according to their requirements.<br/>
<br/>The primary dev tools that we plan to develop are:<br/>
<br/><b>API Tester</b> - This is an obvious addition since we want to support developers.<br/>
<br/><b>Workflow Creator</b> - We have already listed various entities that will be linked centrally forming a star-like topology. But once we add an object or an API defining a process, there has to some way of defining and visualizing their role in an execution pipeline.<br/>
<br/><b>HTML Editor and Coding platform</b> - There are several online HTML and CSS editors and coding platforms connected to Github, Heroku or other platforms for source code management or cloud deployment.<br/>
We wish to provide the same but integrated with our application, so that developers do not have to switch between editors, CI/CD portals or API testers like Jenkins, Gitlab or Postman to deploy and test their APIs in various enviornments.<br/>
There will be a way to ensure that our users are able to maintain different datasets and functionalities that are specific to a particular development environment.

</h4>

